summary: Endgame Writer Says Thor Has Tons Of Guilt For Failing To Go For The Head
title: Endgame Writer Says Thor Has Tons Of Guilt For Failing To Go For The Head
excerpt: Avengers: Endgame co-writer Stephen McFeely has said that Thor has a lot of guilt for his infamous blunder in Avengers: Infinity War.
description:
I don’t like it when Thor is sad. It feels wrong.

I mean it’s not his fault that NO ONE TOLD him Thanos was in Wakanda for like twenty minutes of screen time. He could have saved Vision. Why did no one flag him down then?

Where’s Korg? I think he needs to talk to Korg. Korg understands about his hammer.

summary: Dwayne "The Rock" Johnson Responds to Josh Brolin's Thanos Threat: "I'm Shoving All 6 Stones..."
title: Dwayne "The Rock" Johnson Responds to Josh Brolin's Thanos Threat: "I'm Shoving All 6 Stones..."
body:
Dwayne “The Rock” Johnson Responds to Josh Brolin’s Thanos Threat: “I’m Shoving All 6 Stones…”

Dwayne “The Rock” Johnson, who is slated to play Black Adam, in an upcoming DC movie, responded to Thanos and Cable actor Josh Brolin’s Instagram threat.

After Empire Magazine revealed their Thanos cover, Brolin posted it on Instagram writing, “Eat your heart out @therock. I’m coming for you next, little guy. 😈 #feelgreatlookgreat @empiremagazine”
